• Select Accumulated Dose Alarm visual and/or audio indications:

It is not possible to select the ALARM options when the ALARM set points are lower than the RATE that the unit is exposed to. In this case, raise the ALARM set points in accordance with the previously described steps and then select the desired ALARM options.

The ALARM can be tested by setting the RATE and/or DOSE ALARM set point to zero.

Employment

Select Dose Alarm Visual and/or Audio Indications

  • Ensure the unit is in the Rate mode.
  • Press and hold the ALARM button and then press the DOSE button.
  • Release both buttons and the display will flash the set point value for the Dose Alarm.
  • Set AUD and/or VIS by repeatedly pressing and releasing the ALARM button.
  • It is important that you Do NOT change the Dose Alarm set point that has been previously set.
  • To return to Rate mode, press the RATE button. If the RATE button is not pressed, the unit will return to the RATE mode within 5 seconds.
